      <h5 class="mt-0 mb-1">3.How dangerous is this COVID-19?</h5>
     Like other respiratory ailments, COVID-19 can cause mild symptoms including colds, sore throat, coughing, and fever. About 80% of cases can recover without the need for special care. About 1 out of every 6 people may suffer from severe pain, such as pneumonia or difficulty breathing, which usually occurs gradually. Although the mortality rate for this disease is still low (around 3%), for older people, and people with pre-existing medical conditions (such as diabetes, high blood pressure and heart disease), they are usually more prone to becoming ill severe. Looking at developments to date, more than 50% of confirmed cases have been declared to be improving, and the cure rate will continue to increase.
  </div>
